==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pundit
<hw>Pun"dit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>pandit</ets>, Skr. <ets>pandita</ets> a learned man.]</ety> <def>A
learned man; a teacher; esp., a Brahman versed in the Sanskrit language,
and in the science, laws, and religion of the Hindoos; in Cashmere, any
clerk or native official.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>pandit</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pundle</ent>⟦br⟧
